South Africa&#39;s is making little progress in turning around the economy as political wrangling delays the implementation of reforms, raising the risk of a credit downgrade to sub-investment grade, Standard &amp; Poor&#39;s (S&amp;P&#39;s) Global Ratings said on Thursday. &quot;If things deteriorate further it becomes difficult to continue believing that government can implement the things they say want to do, that they can turn around the economic situation,&quot; said Gardner Rusike, the associate director for S&amp;P&#39;s global ratings.